%U A397543 8,4,8,1,4,3,3,2,7,3,8,9,6,0,9,4,6,0,8,9,6,7
%N A397543 Decimal expansion of the surface area of a canonical (dual-uniform) pentagonal trapezohedron with unit short edge length.
%C A397543 The pentagonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the pentagonal antiprism.
%H A397543 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397543/b397543.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..10000</a>
%H A397543 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/PentagonalTrapezohedron.html">Pentagonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397543 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Pentagonal_antitegum">Pentagonal antitegum</a>.
%H A397543 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397543 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pentagonal_trapezohedron">Pentagonal trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397543 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_04">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 4</a>.
%F A397543 Equals 5*(1 + s)^2*sqrt((1 - s)/2 + s + 2)/4, where s = sqrt(5) = A002163.
%F A397543 Equals the largest root of x^4 - 625*x^2 + 3125.
%e A397543 24.898982848827802734015846213978370554090497058946...
%t A397543 First[RealDigits[Root[#^4 - 625*#^2 + 3125 &, 4], 10, 100]]
%t A397543 (* Alternative: *)
%t A397543 First[RealDigits[PolyhedronData[{"Trapezohedron", 5}, "SurfaceArea"], 10, 100]]
%Y A397543 Cf. A384871 (volume), A237603 (inradius), A239798 (midradius), A397544 (height).
%Y A397543 Cf. A104457 (long edge).
%Y A397543 Cf. A019692 (small face angle * 10), A228719 (large face angle), A137218 (dihedral angle).
%Y A397543 Cf. A384625 (surface area of the dual + 10).
%Y A397543 Cf. A002163.
%K A397543 nonn,cons,easy
%O A397543 2,1
